      "side": 1,
      "message": "It doesn\u0027t matter too much for this CLI program, but I\u0027d like to get you used to context conventions.\n1) strive to only have context.Background() in the main function (or in tests).\n2) if a function needs a context, it should be passed in as the first param, named ctx.\n3) if 2) cannot easily be done, context.TODO() should be used a short-term fix until things can be properly refactored.\n4) Never store context.Context in a struct.\n5) Make use of r.Context() for web requests.\n6) Make use of context.WithTimeout() where appropriate.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 30,
        "startChar": 22,
